    "physiologicalDescription": "Chronic high cortisol, elevated catecholamines, and persistent vasoconstriction may stress arterial linings, potentially interacting with plaque stability and coronary blood flow.",
    "sarcasticAdvice": "CRITICAL CHECKPOINT: Seek immediate emergency medical care. But after you get out of the ICU, do ask yourself if your absolute obsession with productivity, status, and hidden anger was worth a near-death experience. Keep treating your heart like a garbage disposal for stress; I'm sure it will love the next crisis too.",
    "mindfulnessPrompts": [
      "What would my life look like if I stopped treating myself like a high-performance machine and started treating myself like a fragile, lovable human being?",
      "Who or what am I refusing to forgive, choosing instead to let that heavy, angry armor weigh down my chest?"
    ],
    "physicalTherapyTip": "CRITICAL CHECKPOINT: Call emergency services first if experiencing chest pain. For recovery and prevention: practice slow, rhythmic abdominal breathing to lower blood pressure, and perform very gentle chest-opening stretches to release the thoracic cavity.",
    "medical_safety": {
