          "If I allowed myself to say 'No' to what is burning me, how would my chest feel?"
      ],
      "physicalTherapyTip": "For mild reflux support, stay upright after meals, avoid late heavy meals, track triggers, use slower breathing while upright, and seek care for chest pain, trouble swallowing, vomiting blood, black stool, weight loss, or persistent symptoms.",
      "medical_safety": {
          "critical_alerts": [
              "Chest pain, pressure, shortness of breath, sweating, jaw/arm pain, or symptoms that could be heart-related",
              "Trouble swallowing, painful swallowing, choking, or food sticking",
              "Vomiting blood or material that looks like coffee grounds",
              "Black or tarry stool",
              "Unexplained weight loss, persistent vomiting, or severe weakness",
              "Persistent or worsening reflux despite self-care"
