      "tones": {
          "clinical": {
              "mechanism": "Scoliosis is a side-to-side spinal curvature, often with vertebral rotation. It may be idiopathic, congenital, neuromuscular, adolescent, or adult degenerative. Severity is monitored by exam and imaging such as Cobb angle.",
              "protocol": [
                  "Track curve monitoring, age/growth status, pain, uneven shoulders/hips, rib prominence, breathing symptoms, neurologic symptoms, progression, bracing/surgery history, and physical therapy plan.",
