    "id": "seizures",
    "name": "Seizures",
    "category": "General & Energy",
    "emotionalRoot": "Running away from the self. Intense, overwhelming internal pressure, trying to suppress massive emotional trauma or terrifying thoughts until the brain's electrical fuses literally blow under the strain.",
    "metaphor": "Your central nervous system short-circuiting and throwing a massive electrical surge to force a temporary reboot of the mainframe because your conscious mind cannot process the sheer volume of emotional pain.",
    "physiologicalDescription": "Acute emotional or traumatic overload triggers sudden, abnormal, synchronized high-frequency electrical discharges within cortical neurons, temporarily disrupting normal motor, sensory, and cognitive processing.",
    "sarcasticAdvice": "CRITICAL: Seek expert neurological medical care. But do observe how you bottle up your most explosive emotions, fears, and memories inside a tiny airtight jar. I'm sure your nervous system can handle another couple of years of you pretending that nothing is wrong.",
    "mindfulnessPrompts": [
      "What massive, overwhelming fear or ancient memory am I desperately trying to lock away and ignore?",
      "If it were completely safe to let my emotional energy discharge slowly, what tears or screams would finally come out?"
    ],
    "physicalTherapyTip": "Under strict medical guidance, engage in deeply grounding sensory activities, somatic tracking, and daily parasympathetic exercises to widen your nervous system's window of tolerance.",
    "medical_safety": {
      "critical_alerts": [
        "Sudden numbness or weakness of the face, arm, or leg (especially on one side)",
        "Sudden confusion, trouble speaking, or understanding speech",
        "Sudden trouble seeing in one or both eyes",
        "Sudden trouble walking, dizziness, loss of balance, or coordination",
        "Sudden, severe headache with no known cause ('thunderclap' headache)",
        "New onset of facial droop or facial muscle weakness"
      ],
      "seek_immediate_care_if": [
        "You experience sudden facial drooping, arm weakness, or slurred speech (the FAST stroke indicators)",
        "You have a sudden, blindingly severe headache or sudden loss of vision",
        "You experience a seizure, sudden confusion, or loss of consciousness"
      ],
      "schedule_care_if": [
        "You have frequent or progressively worsening headaches that interfere with sleep or work",
        "You experience occasional mild dizziness or subtle changes in coordination or memory",
        "You have persistent jaw pain or clicking that does not improve with stress reduction"
      ],
      "self_care_allowed_if": "Mild, familiar headaches or muscle tension may respond well to rest, hydration, and gentle massage.",
      "do_not_ignore": "Sudden neurological deficits or severe headaches must be immediately evaluated to rule out stroke, aneurysm, or other brain emergencies.",
      "disclaimer": "This app is for education and self-reflection only. It does not diagnose, treat, prevent, or cure disease. Seek professional medical care for diagnosis, treatment, medication decisions, or urgent symptoms."
    }
  },
